---
import Main from "../layouts/Main.astro";
---

<Main title="print-out-page">
  <div
    class="w-[8.5in] h-[11in] border-2 border-textColor grayscale m-auto bg-bg invert"
  >
    <div class="p-4 card w-full h-full flex flex-col text-lg">
      <div class="flex flex-col mb-2 pb-1 border-b mb-8">
        <h1 class="uppercase text-3xl font-bold">>: Unplatform</h1>
        <p class="text-center font-bold mb-2 italic">
          Q: How do I find cool stuff outside of social media?
        </p>
        <p class="text-center font-bold mb-2">
          A: It's easy. Let's walk you through it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-0.5">
        <div>
          <h2 class="pb-1 border-b border-text font-bold mb-2">
            Q: How do I ... <span class="italic">~ find events? ~</span>
          </h2>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-4 flex flex-col gap-2">
            <li>
              <p>
                <b>nonsense</b> (https://nonsensenyc.com/): An mailing list focused
                on independent art and culture events in NYC.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <b>red cal</b> (https://cal.red): Find events with cool music, community
                engagement, and radical politics.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <b>NYC Off-Tech</b> (https://buttondown.com/nycofftech/): Find events
                dedicated to building off-platform and offline community.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <b>NYC Noise</b> (https://nyc-noise.com/): A music events calendar
                with a focus on DIY music & artists. Also includes a massive directory
                of other similar event calendars from around the world.
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <p>
                <b>the skint</b> (https://www.theskint.com/): An NYC events calendar
                that focuses on low-cost events.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="pb-1 border-b border-text font-bold mb-2">
            Q: How do I ... <span class="italic">~ read the news? ~</span>
          </h2>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-4 flex flex-col gap-2">
            <li>
              <p>
                <b>hell gate</b> (https://hellgatenyc.com): A worker-owned local paper.
                Covers politics, culture, and entertainment.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <b>gothamist</b> (https://gothamist.com/): A non-profit newsroom run
                by WNYC.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2 class="pb-1 border-b border-text font-bold mb-2">
            Q: How do I ... <span class="italic">~ keep up with friends? ~</span
            >
          </h2>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-4 flex flex-col gap-2">
            <li>
              <p>
                <b>letterloop</b> (https://www.letterloop.co/): Keep up with friends,
                family, or whoever else on your own private newsletter.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                <b>calling</b> (your phone number): When's the last time you called
                a friend?
              </p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="my-1">
        <h2 class="border-text pb-1 border-b font-bold mb-1">
          Q: How do I ... <span class="italic">~ learn more? ~</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="font-bold text-center">
          https://unplatform.fromthesuperhighway.com
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <style>
    .card:nth-child(1),
    .card:nth-child(2) {
      border-bottom: 2px solid white;
    }
    .card:nth-child(2),
    .card:nth-child(4) {
      border-left: 1px solid white;
    }

    .card:nth-child(1),
    .card:nth-child(3) {
      border-right: 1px solid white;
    }
  </style>
</Main>
